        <p>The attestation chain for educational documents often starts with verification by the issuing institution. Some countries require the university to verify the degree before the attestation process can begin. We advise on these preliminary requirements based on your specific institution and country.</p>
        
        <p>For <a href="/services/golden-visa-translation/">Golden Visa applications</a>, educational documents need both attestation and MOHESR equivalency. We coordinate both processes to ensure your documents meet all requirements.</p>
        
        <h3>Personal Status Documents</h3>
        <p><a href="/personal/vital-records/birth/">Birth certificates</a>, <a href="/personal/vital-records/marriage/">marriage certificates</a>, and <a href="/personal/vital-records/divorce/">divorce decrees</a> frequently need attestation for immigration, family sponsorship, and personal status proceedings in the UAE.</p>
        
        <p>These documents often require translation as well as attestation. The translation may need to happen before or after certain attestation steps depending on the document and country of origin. We ensure the correct sequence is followed.</p>
        
        <p>For marriage certificates from countries that do not issue separate documents, attestation of the official record extract may be required. We understand these variations and advise accordingly.</p>
        
        <h3>Commercial and Corporate Documents</h3>
        <p>Trade licenses, <a href="/legal/corporate/moa/">Memoranda of Association</a>, board resolutions, and commercial contracts may need attestation for use in UAE business contexts. Requirements vary based on the intended use—whether for company registration, banking relationships, or legal proceedings.</p>
        
        <p>Powers of Attorney for business purposes often require attestation when created abroad. <a href="/legal/corporate/poa/">POA attestation</a> follows the same chain as other documents but may have additional requirements depending on the specific powers granted.</p>
        
        <h3>Police Clearance Certificates</h3>
        <p><a href="/personal/immigration/pcc/">Police clearance certificates</a> are required for many UAE visa applications. These documents typically have validity periods, so timing the attestation process is important—you do not want the certificate to expire during the attestation chain.</p>
        
        <p>We advise on realistic timelines for PCC attestation based on your country of origin and current processing times, helping you plan the application sequence appropriately.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

