        <p>Educational documents from the UK may also require Chartered Institute verification or HEA confirmation depending on the institution. We advise on these additional requirements when applicable.</p>
        
        <h3>India</h3>
        <p>India joined the Hague Convention in 2005, so Indian documents can now be Apostilled rather than requiring embassy attestation. The Ministry of External Affairs handles Apostilles through regional passport offices. Processing typically takes 7-14 days.</p>
        
        <p>Educational documents from India often require verification from the issuing university and HRD (Human Resource Development) attestation before Apostille. We coordinate this complete chain.</p>
        
        <h3>Pakistan</h3>
        <p>Pakistan has not joined the Hague Convention, so documents require traditional embassy attestation. The chain includes: Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Pakistan), UAE Embassy (Islamabad or Karachi), and MOFA (UAE). Processing typically takes 3-5 weeks.</p>
        
        <p>We work with established partners in Pakistan who handle attestation requests regularly and can navigate the specific requirements efficiently.</p>
        
        <h3>Egypt and Other Arab Countries</h3>
        <p>Several Arab countries have reciprocal attestation agreements with the UAE that may simplify certain requirements. The specific process depends on the document type and current bilateral arrangements. We advise based on current practice rather than outdated information.</p>
        
        <h3>Other Countries</h3>
        <p>We handle documents from virtually any country. For less common source countries, we research current requirements and connect with reliable local partners to ensure proper attestation. Processing times vary but we provide realistic estimates based on current conditions.</p>
      </div>
